!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

foolish /ˈfuːlɪʃ/

1. ADJ If someone's behaviour or action is foolish , it is not sensible and shows a lack of good judgment. 愚蠢的 

例： It would be foolish to raise hopes unnecessarily. 无缘无故地寄托希望是愚蠢的。 

2. foolishly ADV 愚蠢地 

例： He admitted that he had acted foolishly. 他承认自己做得很愚蠢。 

3. ADJ If you look or feel foolish , you look or feel so silly or ridiculous that people are likely to laugh at you. 傻乎乎的 

例： I just stood there feeling foolish and watching him. 我就傻乎乎地站在那儿看着他。 

4. foolishly ADV 傻乎乎地 [ADV after v] 

例： He saw me standing there, grinning foolishly at him. 他看到我站在那儿咧着嘴朝他傻乎乎地笑。

</div>

